Program: Outlook
Title: If you don't pick cotton, you're fired
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00yhnxg
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 3 Oct 2012
A nurse in Uzbekistan describes how medical staff are being sent to the cotton fields to help with this year's harvest. Also, a Syrian family in California tell us about adapting to their new life and their fears for those they have left behind. And Carrie Waley, born in China and now living in the UK, on trying to explain the Chinese to the British and vice versa. Show less